reactLuauPropsHelper.props.markdownDescription:
Per-class prop list. Each entry overrides the built-in defaults for that class — presence of a key is authoritative, so an explicit empty array (`[]`) disables completions for that class. Custom component identifiers (e.g. `MyButton`) can be added here too. Two shapes:

```jsonc
{
  // Array form: just the prop list.
  "TextLabel": ["Text", "TextColor3"],
  "MyButton": ["label", "onClick", "disabled"],
  // Object form: extend a class and add extras.
  "GamepassCard": { "extends": "Frame", "props": ["gamepassId"] }
}
```

Most custom components don't need this — the extension can usually infer props from in-file annotations, typed signatures, or the component's root `createElement` call. Use config when the component lives in a file the extension can't reach or when you want central overrides.
